--><!--introduction-->
<p>This script works by using intensity thresholding to choose how to color certain areas of the image. It intelligently divides the image into regions, and paints the regions with the average RGB values present there.</p>
<!--/introduction--><h2>Initialize<a name="1"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

clc;clear;close all
image = 'climb.jpg';
% There is a bit of hyperparameter tuning with this script. the% smoot_factor represents how much to smooth the intensity histogram, and% the peak_prom is the prominence of valleys in the intensity histogram to% treat as a separate bin.
smooth_factor = 20;
peak_prom = 10000;
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Load the Image<a name="2"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

im = imread(image);
% im = rot90(im,-1); % Some images need to be rotated
im_gray = rgb2gray(im); % Convert to grayscale
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Histogram<a name="3"></a></h2>
<p>Create a histogram of intensity values and smooth it.</p>

{% highlight matlab %}

[counts,binLocations] = imhist(im_gray);
c = smooth(counts,smooth_factor);
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Identify Bins<a name="4"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

symm = [flipud(c);c; flipud(c)];
[~,loc] = findpeaks(symm,'MinPeakProminence',peak_prom);
peaks = loc(loc-256 &gt;0 &amp; loc-256&lt;=256)-256;
symm = max(symm)-symm;
[~,loc] = findpeaks(symm,'MinPeakProminence',peak_prom);
valleys = loc(loc-256 &gt;= 0 &amp; loc-256&lt;=256)-256;
if valleys(1) == 0
    valleys(1) = 1;
endif valleys(end) ~= 256
    valleys = [valleys; 256];
endif peaks(1) == 0
    peaks(1) = 1;
endif peaks(end) ~= 256
    peaks = [peaks; 256];
end

ind = valleys;
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Average RGB Values<a name="5"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

new_im = im;
r = new_im(:,:,1);
g = new_im(:,:,2);
b = new_im(:,:,3);
new_r = r;
new_g = g;
new_b = b;

for i = 1:length(ind)-1
    t1 = (ind(i)-1);
    t2 = (ind(i+1)-1);
    img = im_gray &gt; t1 &amp; im_gray &lt; t2;
    mask = not(logical(img));
    r_i = r(mask);
    g_i = g(mask);
    b_i = b(mask);
    cols = [mean(r_i) mean(g_i) mean(b_i)];
    new_r(mask) = cols(1);
    new_g(mask) = cols(2);
    new_b(mask) = cols(3);
end

new_im(:,:,1) = new_r;
new_im(:,:,2) = new_g;
new_im(:,:,3) = new_b;
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Results<a name="6"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

figure
imshow(im);
figure
imshow(new_im);
{% endhighlight %}
